In this press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney announces that President Obama will be traveling to New York to view recovery efforts after Hurricane Sandy. Carney also discusses the President's stance on the fiscal cliff negotiations, stating that the President would veto any bill that extends the Bush-era tax cuts for the top 2 percent of earners. Carney emphasizes the importance of passing tax cuts for 98 percent of Americans and highlights the need for a balanced approach to addressing the fiscal challenges facing the country. The press briefing also includes discussions on General Petraeus's resignation as CIA Director and the President's upcoming trips to Asia.